1 """
2 This script is the output of my frustration with Gazebo,
3 when I want to place reusable blocks, which passing some
4 strings as parameters. Also to change origin and orientation
5 using quaternion mathematics. Wish me luck.
6 
7 Usage:
8 1) Make the required changes in generate_xacro class's __init__
9 definition constants and just run the python file. This
10 will take panda_arm_reference.xacro as base, generated required
11 xacro blocks and rewrites the old panda_arm.xacro. So
12 make a backup of working and stable panda_arm.xacro before
13 attempting to do any changes for peace of your own mind.
14 2) You don't need to run the python file every time, only
15 when you want to change the xacro settings
16 3) If you want to change the xacro, you can, but later
17 update the changes in this file's xacro template, so that next
18 time they are auto-magically generated for you
19 4) This python file should be one stop destination
20 relating to generating the xacro for all needs
21 5) The variables are named programmatically and clearly,
22 so I won't comment. Everything is self explanatory
23 """

158 def list_to_string(my_list):
159  """
160  Input a list, it will output a string delimited by a white space
161  :param my_list: list
162  list of floats like [0.2 0.3 0.4]
163  :return: str
164  Returns literally 0.2 0.3 0.4 in a string format
165  """
166  return ' '.join([str(each_item) for each_item in my_list])

399  def write_config(self):

405  script_directory = os.path.dirname(os.path.realpath(__file__))
